 | SERT ([[SLC6A4]]) || || 17q11.2  || This gene locus has been associated with rigid-compulsive behaviors. Notably, it has also been associated with [[clinical depression|depression]] but only as a result of social adversity, although other studies have found no link.<ref>{{vcite journal |author=Surtees PG, Wainwright NW, Willis-Owen SA, Luben R, [[Nick Day|Day NE]], Flint J |title=Social adversity, the serotonin transporter (5-HTTLPR) polymorphism and major depressive disorder |journal=Biol Psychiatry |volume=59 |issue=3 |pages=224–9 |year=2006 |pmid=16154545 |doi=10.1016/j.biopsych.2005.07.014}}</ref>  Significant linkage in families with only affected males has been shown.<ref>{{vcite journal |author=Sutcliffe JS, Delahanty RJ, Prasad HC, ''et al.'' |author.= |title=Allelic heterogeneity at the serotonin transporter locus (SLC6A4) confers susceptibility to autism and rigid-compulsive behaviors |journal=Am J Hum Genet |volume=77 |issue=2 |pages=265–79 |year=2005 |pmid=15995945 |doi=10.1086/432648}}</ref><ref>{{vcite journal |author=Devlin B, Cook EH, Coon H, ''et al.'' |author.= |title=Autism and the serotonin transporter: the long and short of it |journal=Mol Psychiatry |volume=10 |issue=12 |pages=1110–6 |year=2005 |pmid=16103890 |doi=10.1038/sj.mp.4001724}}</ref>  Researchers have also suggested that the gene contributes to [[serotonin syndrome|hyperserotonemia]].<ref>{{vcite journal |author=Coutinho AM, Oliveira G, Morgadinho T, ''et al.'' |author.= |title=Variants of the serotonin transporter gene (SLC6A4) significantly contribute to hyperserotonemia in autism |journal=Mol Psychiatry |volume=9 |issue=3 |pages=264–71 |year=2004 |pmid=15094787 |doi=10.1038/sj.mp.4001409}}</ref> However, a 2008 meta-analysis of family- and population-based studies found no significant overall association between autism and either the promoter insertion/deletion ([[5-HTTLPR]]) or the intron 2 VNTR (STin2 VNTR) polymorphisms.<ref>{{vcite journal |journal= Am J Med Genet B Neuropsychiatr Genet |volume=147B |issue=6 |pages=903–13 |date=2008 |title= Autism and serotonin transporter gene polymorphisms: a systematic review and meta-analysis |author= Huang CH, Santangelo SL |doi=10.1002/ajmg.b.30720 |pmid=18286633}}</ref>
