 | [[CACNA1G]] || || 17q21.33 || Markers within an interval containing this gene are associated with ASD at a locally significant level. The region likely harbors a combination of multiple rare and common alleles that contribute to genetic risk for ASD.<ref>{{vcite journal |author= Strom SP, Stone JL, ten Bosch JR ''et al.'' |author.= |title= High-density SNP association study of the 17q21 chromosomal region linked to autism identifies ''CACNA1G'' as a novel candidate gene |journal= Mol Psychiatry |year=2009 |volume= |issue= |pages=  |pmid= |doi=10.1038/mp.2009.41 |laysummary=http://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2009-05/uoc--ngl051809.php |laysource=Press release |laydate=2009-05-19}}</ref>
