 | [[PRKCB1]] || || 16p11.2 || Philippi ''et al.'' (2005) found a strong association between this gene and autism. This is a recent finding that needs to be replicated.<ref>{{vcite journal |author=Philippi A, Roschmann E, Tores F, ''et al.'' |author.= |title=Haplotypes in the gene encoding protein kinase c-beta (PRKCB1) on chromosome 16 are associated with autism |journal=Mol Psychiatry |volume=10 |issue=10 |pages=950–60 |year=2005 |pmid=16027742 |doi=10.1038/sj.mp.4001704}}</ref>
